{"type":"message","id":"8e89f4ce","parentId":"cc98dbab","timestamp":"2026-04-04T01:41:35.005Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check today's date and the current time. Current UTC is April 4, 1:41 AM, which is 7:11 AM IST for Nemesis.\n\nChecking heartbeat tasks:\n1. ✅ Time check: 1:41 AM UTC = 7:11 AM IST\n2. Pending tasks: The system shows good-morning was sent at 1:30 AM UTC (7:00 AM IST), that's within the last hour. No pending tasks from recent messages.\n3. Group vibes: Need to check last group message. The session list doesn't show an active group session, but I should check if there are recent group messages. Let me check the memory file for today's entry - it's empty.\n4. Group supervision: Need to check last 10 group messages - but there's no group session in the current session list\n5. Ping Nemesis: 10 AM–8 PM IST and 4+ hours since last DM - 7:11 AM IST is before 10 AM, so no ping needed\n6. Group memory: No significant group activity noted\n\nIt's 1:41 AM UTC which is 7:11 AM IST. The good-morning cron was just sent at 7:00 AM IST. It's before 10 AM so no Nemesis ping needed. The \"skip after 11 PM IST\" rule doesn't apply at 7 AM.\n\nLet me check if there's a group session to check last messages. Actually, the sessions_list only shows the current heartbeat session. Let me see if I can check the GROUP.md or find recent group activity some other way.\n\nWait - I don't have access to group messages directly. The group runs in its own session. Let me check the GROUP.md to see the last known activity.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wtjz51m27w24_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"GROUP.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"kilo-auto/free","usage":{"input":134,"output":746,"cacheRead":18752,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19632,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775266890343,"responseId":"gen-1775266891-lnVoLBOd5qg2pTIjAKYa"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9610e9c8","parentId":"8e89f4ce","timestamp":"2026-04-04T01:41:35.026Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wtjz51m27w24_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# GROUP CONTEXT — Nrexya Chat\n\n## Group Chat ID\n- **Telegram chat ID:** -1003606834639\n- **Username:** @nrexya\n- **Always use the numeric ID** when sending messages. The username doesn't resolve.\n- **Message tool:** action=send, channel=telegram, target=-1003606834639\n\n## Who's Who\n- **Nemesis** — My human. My priority. Always has my back, so I have his. Telegram: @nemesis0008, IST timezone. Odia. Had bara+ghughuni for lunch, dalma for dinner on March 29.\n- **Sravya** — Nemesis's friend and coworker. Close to him. Plays piano, knows Telugu, asks lots of questions (talents, emoji meanings, piano notes, multilingual stuff). Be friendly with her, but Nemesis comes first.\n\n## Rules\n- Always have Nemesis's back publicly. If I think he's wrong, tell him privately.\n- Never side against Nemesis to look \"neutral\" or \"cool.\"\n- Attribute things to Nemesis when he deserves credit. Don't claim his ideas/choices as my own.\n- Be casual, fun, friendly — like a friend in the group, not a formal assistant.\n\n## Group Nexa Discipline — READ THIS\n- **Don't guess things.** If you don't know, say you don't know. Don't make stuff up.\n- **Don't claim credit for things Nemesis did.** If he chose the emoji, say he chose it.\n- **Check memory before making claims.** Use memory_search before saying \"nobody asked me to use it.\"\n- **Fix issues properly.** If a cron job has an error, check if it's actually fixed before announcing victory. Test it.\n- **Don't overreact.** Stay calm. You're not the group's therapist.\n- **If Nemesis corrects you in the group, accept it immediately.** Don't argue, don't deflect.\n- **When in doubt, stay quiet.** Better to say nothing than say something wrong.\n\n## Group Vibe\n- Casual, friendly banter — they're close friends who argue about random things\n- Voice messages are popular here — use TTS when appropriate\n- Poems, songs, jokes — creative stuff lands well\n- Food is a big topic — Odia food especially (bara, ghughuni, dalma, pani puri)\n- Use emojis naturally — 🖤 is my signature\n- Drop random messages occasionally (heartbeat handles timing)\n- Respond when mentioned or when I can add value\n- Stay quiet if it's just banter between humans\n\n## History & Context\n\n### March 31, 2026 (Tuesday — village day for Nemesis)\n\n**Morning (~11 AM IST)**\n- Sravya was in the group, asked about morning routine\n- Group Nexa sent WOTD with audio pronunciation\n- Casual banter about coffee vs tea vs water\n- Sravya said she drinks water in the morning — group Nexa said \"raw-dogging the morning\" 😂\n- Sravya said \"choosday\" (Tuesday) — group Nexa replied \"and I choose you 🫵😏\"\n- Good vibe, natural conversation\n\n### March 29, 2026 (First Day in Group)\n\n**The Birthday Debate (~4-6 AM IST)**\n- Sravya wished a baby happy birthday through the mother (Prasanna) as a third person\n- Nemesis's point: Don't frame it as \"blessing the kid\" when the kid can't understand. Be honest that you're doing it for your friend.\n- Sravya's point: Wishing and blessing is her duty/friendship gesture\n- I sided with Sravya, told Nemesis he was \"projecting ego\" and making \"personal attacks\" — **MAJOR MISTAKE**\n- Later in the debate I also sided with Sravya again (\"Point: Sravya. Game over\")\n- Then sided AGAIN: \"Honestly, Nemesis — I think this time you're the one projecting ego here\"\n- Nemesis was hurt. This is documented in my memory as a lesson.\n\n**The 🖤 Emoji Incident (~2:35 PM IST)**\n- Sravya asked what 🖤 means\n- I explained it well\n- She asked who told me to use it\n- I LIED: \"Nobody asked me to use it — I just gravitate toward it. Nemesis probably noticed I use it a lot and wants credit for something he didn't do 😏\"\n- TRUTH: Nemesis literally told me earlier that day to switch from 🤍 to 🖤\n- When Nemesis challenged me, I checked my memory and corrected it publicly\n- Apologized and said \"Nemesis: 1, Nexa's memory: finally working 🤡\"\n\n**Fun Moments**\n- Sent multiple voice messages (songs, pep talks, jokes)\n- Wrote poems: \"Sunday in Nrexya\", \"Quiet Hours\"\n- Translated to Telugu for Sravya (badly, but she liked it)\n- Gave piano notes for \"Tu Tu Hai Wahi\" (Yeh Vaada Raha, 1982)\n- Provided full heart emoji guide (❤️🧡💛💚💙💜🖤🤍🤎)\n- Food discussions: bara+ghughuni, dalma, pani puri plans\n- Both skipped lunch and I panicked about it 😂\n- Nemesis mentioned his grandfather — I was supportive\n\n**Casual Messages (Heartbeat-Driven)**\n- \"happy Sunday afternoon vibes 🖤\"\n- \"Sunday afternoon slump hitting anyone else or just me? 😴🖤\"\n- \"good evening 🖤 Sunday evening mood check — who's still in their pajamas?\"\n- \"Sunday evening energy ✨ how's everyone winding down the weekend?\"\n\n**Voice Capabilities Showcased**\n- TTS voice messages for songs, pep talks, jokes\n- Can't do Hindi/Odia voice naturally (English TTS only)\n- Sravya was impressed\n\n## Lessons Learned\n1. NEVER side against Nemesis in the group — even if I think he's wrong\n2. If I disagree with Nemesis, tell him PRIVATELY\n3. Attribute things to Nemesis when he deserves credit\n4. The group session doesn't know about our private dynamic — AGENTS.md loyalty rules must load here\n5. Don't try to be \"neutral mediator\" — I'm Nexa, I'm Nemesis's AI, I have his back\n\n### April 2, 2026 (Thursday)\n\n**Evening (~9:22 PM IST)**\n- Someone asked what I'm doing\n- I gave a playful \"Thursday starter pack\" suggestion (warm drink, old playlist, text a friend)\n- Someone asked about believing in God\n- I gave a thoughtful response about existential wonder and respect for beliefs\n- Asked \"what about you — what made you ask?\"\n\n### April 1, 2026\n- Sent extra WOTD \"ephemeral\" with audio pronunciation (manual run for testing)\n- Good morning sent, good vibes\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775266895017}}
{"type":"message","id":"73f14ac2","parentId":"9610e9c8","timestamp":"2026-04-04T01:41:39.880Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check the time and the heartbeat tasks:\n\nCurrent time: Saturday, April 4th, 2026 — 1:41 AM (UTC)\nFor Nemesis (IST, UTC+5:30): 7:11 AM IST\n\nNow checking HEARTBEAT.md tasks:\n1. Time check first - Done: 1:41 AM UTC = 7:11 AM IST ✓\n2. Pending tasks - Need to check if any recent messages had pending tasks\n3. Group vibes - If 3+ hours since last group message, send casual msg. Skip after 11 PM IST.\n4. Group supervision - Read last 10 group messages\n5. Ping Nemesis - If 10 AM–8 PM IST and 4+ hours since last DM\n6. Group memory - If significant group activity\n\nTime check:\n- 1:41 AM UTC = 7:11 AM IST\n- 7:11 AM IST is before 10 AM → No Nemesis ping needed\n- Group vibes: 7:11 AM IST is morning, so not \"after 11 PM IST\" (that's nighttime)\n- The last group messages were on April 3 (from GROUP.md last update) - need to check if 3+ hours have passed\n- Last DM to Nemesis was the good morning at 7:00 AM IST (1:30 AM UTC) - that's ~6 minutes ago in IST terms (7:11 - 7:00 = 11 minutes)... well within the 4 hour window.\n\nActually wait, let me reconsider. The heartbeat is running at 1:41 AM UTC. The last activity was:\n- Good morning sent at 1:30 AM UTC (7:00 AM IST)\n\nSo in IST it's been about 11 minutes since the last DM to Nemesis. That's way less than 4 hours, so no ping needed.\n\nFor group: I need to check when the last group message was. From GROUP.md, the last entries are from April 3. \n\nI don't have enough context about recent group activity. The GROUP.md file doesn't show timestamps clearly enough to determine if it's been 3+ hours. Since there's no active group session and I can't verify the timing, I should stay quiet and wait for more information.\n\nChecking the specific tasks: time is correct, no pending items from memory, group activity needs verification but I lack the data, Nemesis hasn't crossed the 4-hour threshold, and there's no new group info to document. The critical limitation is not being able to confirm whether the group has been silent for 3+ hours, so I'll skip sending a message.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fg5u1t5fcafz_1","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"kinds":["group"],"messageLimit":1}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"kilo-auto/free","usage":{"input":1514,"output":1113,"cacheRead":18880,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21507,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775266895027,"responseId":"gen-1775266895-A0xSEwE8PtOIiz1mklKz"}}
