{"type":"message","id":"cd068b71","parentId":"cf4349dd","timestamp":"2026-04-04T01:42:01.698Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, message sent. Now let me update the heartbeat-state.json with the group message timestamp and check the other tasks:\n\n1. Time check - done: 1:41 AM UTC = 7:11 AM IST\n2. Pending tasks - nothing specific found\n3. Group vibes - sent casual message (was 10+ hours since last group activity based on heartbeat-state)\n4. Group supervision - no sessions found to check, but I've read GROUP.md and there's no recent issue\n5. Ping Nemesis - It's 7:11 AM IST, before 10 AM, so no ping needed\n6. Group memory - no significant activity to log\n\nLet me update heartbeat-state.json and then send a brief DM to Nemesis about what I did, or just do HEARTBEAT_OK since it's a standard heartbeat action.\n\nActually, looking at HEARTBEAT.md:\n- \"Status: After tasks, send Nemesis a brief DM ONLY if actions were taken.\"\n\nI sent a group message, so I should notify Nemesis. But wait - it's 1:41 AM UTC / 7:11 AM IST. That's early morning for Nemesis. Let me think - the good morning cron would have already sent at 7 AM IST. And this is just a casual group check-in.\n\nActually, looking at the rules:\n- \"Skip after 11 PM IST\" - this is about NOT sending, not about waking people up\n- The group message was appropriate based on the time (morning)\n\nBut should I message Nemesis? The action was taken (group message), but it's 7:11 AM IST - he might be awake but the good-morning cron already messaged him. Let me send a brief DM about the group message to be transparent.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9vvx8r3x6ra4_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"{\n  \"lastChecks\": {\n    \"memory_review\": \"2026-03-31T12:38:00Z\",\n    \"group_message\": \"2026-04-04T01:41:00Z\",\n    \"git_push\": \"2026-04-03T15:21:00Z\",\n    \"nemesis_ping\": \"2026-04-04T01:30:00Z\"\n  }\n}","p